"Expenses to date?"
Each passed a chit to Stephen again and he began to work out figures on his stylish
little HP 70 calculator, the digits glowing red in the dimly lit room.
"The shares cost us one million dollars. Expenses to date are $142 so Mr. Metcalfe is in
