"Oh, do I?" said Stephen. "I also require someone in London to send the necessary
telegram. That will be you, Jean Pierre."
"Understood," said Jean Pierre.
For nearly an hour the others asked several questions of detail in order to be as
familiar with the plan as Stephen was.
James's mind drifted again, hoping the earth would open up. He even began to wish
