"Yes, yes," said Jean Pierre. "The chap who's been taking care of Nixon."
"My God, what a piece of luck. We couldn't have anyone better, but he's very
expensive."
"I don't give a damn about the expense," wailed Harvey.
"Well, it might be as high as fifty thousand dollars."
