on his guests.
"Very generous, Harvey. Typical of your reputation." Nick Lloyd gave Michael Hogan a
knowing look. Even if the others didn't, they knew what was typical of his reputation.
The chauffeur returned to report that there was no trace of a solitary professor
anywhere in the champagne bar, balcony luncheon room or the paddock buffet, and
he'd been unable to gain access to the Members' Enclosure.
"Naturally not," said Harvey in a rather pompous manner. "I shall have to find him
myself. Drink up and enjoy yourselves."
Harvey rose and walked to the door with the chauffeur. Once he was out of earshot of
his guests, he said:
"Get your ass out of here and don't give me any crap about not being able to find him."
The chauffeur bolted. Harvey turned to his guests and smiled.
