"I am going to look at the runners and riders for the two o'clock."
"He's leaving the box now," said James.
"What's that you're saying?" asked the Duke of Rutland. "Are you talking to yourself,
James?"
James stared at the noble Duke, six foot one and still able to stand his full height, an M.
C. and a D.S.O. in the First World War. Although the lines on liis face suggested that
he had passed the age at which the Maker had fulfilled his contract, he sail exuded
