Stephen had completed his task and was determined to get out before any mistakes
could be made. He knew Harold Macmillan would shake hands with and talk to over a
thousand people by the time the day was over and his chances of remembering Harvey
were minimal. In any case, it would not much matter if he did. Harvey was, after all, a
genuine benefactor of Harvard.
"We ought to leave before the senior people, Mr. Metcalfe."
"Of course, Rod. You're the boss."
"I think that would be wise."
